        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 7:31AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 730 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
southwest of St. Paul, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Dutton...                         Withrow Springs State Park...
Huntsville...                     Dryfork...
St. Paul...                       Japton...
Kingston...                       Delaney...
Witter...                         Marble...
Brashears...                      Forum...
Aurora...                         Alabam...
Patrick...                        Combs...
Georgetown...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 AM CDT for
northwestern and west central Arkansas.</instruction>
